The paper focuses on the task of grounding natural language entities in images, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed approach involves deep learning techniques, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses related work on cross-modal retrieval and image captioning, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
